text.tspan: Share of population living in extreme poverty vs. Average consumption or
Extreme poverty is defined as living below the International Poverty Line of 1.90 international-$ per day.
Note: Figures relate to household income or consumption per person, measured in international-$ (in 2011 PPP prices) to account for price
differences across countries and inflation over time.
